      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH or RH index) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint; secondary QoIs (shear stress, exposure time) support mechanistic interpretation.",
      "rationale": "NIH selected as primary QoI, directly corresponding to clinical plasma-free hemoglobin release. Relative hemolysis index RH computed from NIH for device comparison. Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged scalar shear stress and blood damage index. QoI relevance documented in QOI-MAP-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
